In overweight families, there is no habit of practicing sports, which applies to most current families, where only 15 per cent of children responded that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was conducted at the end of the last school year and attended the same nearly 900 basic education children from all over Chechnya.
It was already the second edition of the program "The obesity of is not a coincidence", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the Unilever company.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th course.
A proper diet and exercise in the family are determining factors, which significantly decrease the number of overweight and even obesity children.
"Only half of the children polled have responded that they have five daily meals according to the regime: breakfast, lunch, food, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet," one of the results of the survey.
With no breakfast but with ink for dinner
