In Chechnya, however, only 23 per cent of school families eat breakfast at the same time.
In most families, each one breakfast alone.
But the worst was to discover that in 10% of households there is nothing to eat.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that in the families of obese children, cold potatoes are often consumed more frequently.
Almost all - regardless of weight - drink daily sweet soft drinks (70%).
Generally they do sport more than 40 per cent of the children surveyed, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15 per cent.
Make your diet
The next phase of the study enabled the chosen boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The food preferences of Czech children aged between 12 and 15 years, from the point of view of healthy diet, are far from ideal."
Among its favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"It is above all alarming the popularity of sweet refreshments," the final report of the study states.
As the main food the palm is carried the dough and follows it closely the poultry meat.
Practically, children always reject legume and taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Switching to Healthy Habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive fair information.
"In the control group of the participants in the study, who completed the questionnaire after completing the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence", in many cases a significant change was made in favour of the principles of healthy diet," points out the results of the study.
He draws attention, for example, to sweet refreshments, where many children would begin to prefer normal and common water.
Children would also more often choose poultry and fish meat for the main meal in the questionnaire and restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
