On the other hand, in the mountains you have to be careful not to bury an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There's only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to advance to a number of required rivals (the normal in a classic race), then try to make time (the classic timed due) and then wait for a duel against a single opponent.
In the midst of all this, sometimes the police appear, which only makes things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button right at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are quite fewer landscapes in the game of what might be expected (in particular there are only three).
But the final result is positive, because this element does not get upset and, in the context already mentioned, it is one of the elements that makes the game more interesting.
The driving model follows the tracks of previous episodes.
That means that it is no longer a big deal today, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you're looking for a realistic simulation, you can look elsewhere.
But a career conceived with a lot of action is quite suitable for this style of driving, although we can find something better among the games of competition.
So far, everything's in order.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, the same is no longer the case with collisions.
Of games of this kind you can't expect to recreate deformations and complicated collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you can't predict how your car will react, which is not everything in order.
It is typical that, by making a very adjusted advance or circulating the car with a normal traffic, there are only slight rocks, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up doing uncontrolled piruettes.
It even ends up completely destroyed.
Thanks to the diet system, there are no great problems, but you can get in the wrong mood.
The snacks are scheduled in such a way that when you suffer an accident or get out of the track, the game returns you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, only five recipes are available in each race.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it's just help in case something isn't right, but it's not very reliable.
Sometimes, nor reseteo helps, only helps to learn the given stage of memory.
A great disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to go in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Sometimes you'll find yourself on some "civil" vehicle site with the same configuration, even if you're the first, fifth, or you'll be five minutes before or after.
This makes it anger especially in situations, when you see two cars going to meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you get there, you have to turn or stop.
It's the same when you get here, because it's programmed that the "surprise" will always happen in front of your noses.
The opponents also have one more advantage.
Throughout the trip you will reach places where, regardless of the moment, you will always advance the same opponent on the same site.
This also happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must arrive before you, at any price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming in front of you, so at first you can make the car paper.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspension and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that you are likely to be disappointed immediately.
And it's a shame, because even though the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and with action, so it's often not possible to follow the detail what happens or where.
And it really does the same, if merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or ranking in the race so that it doesn't get bored, or anything else.
An unusual idea is the change of cars during racing.
You have to be aware of the gas lifts next to the road, because right there you have to change cars, although in most cases you will have enough of what you have.
The cars are divided into three categories.
Sports are suitable for urban areas, for strong American cars for straight highways and for exotic supersports for technical driving, for example by mountain roads with curves.
In addition, the main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, i.e., there are races in specific places that you will know by the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also points of experience for your profile, which serves both the challenges and the stories.
Upon reaching the top level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and finishing with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an Autolog online feature is connected, which compares your results with that of other players and provides other community functions.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race is made in history.
With the car you reach the metro tunnel (pass), where you run in the dark through the tracks (pass).
The speed meter marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (passe) and, suddenly, the metro convoy arrives behind you and you are taken ahead of you without more.
In the writing we will probably have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the game programming no one thought even a little or if the authors actually take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects result in most pleasant cases, sometimes even superb.
For what a pity that, at the most tense times, the quality of the image is reduced and, at times, in a serious manner.
This mainly affects accidents where many participants are involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is good and the soundtrack is a question of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each one of his father and mother", but it may be assumed that no one would buy the game just for his music.
The final feeling of Need for Speed: The Run is therefore quite confused.
If the game avoided absolutely foolish mistakes, we would have trouble saying that The Run is the best NFS game in recent years.
It gives the feeling that the game is not over.
Fun is assured, but be prepared because mistakes will hit you in the eyes with the strength of a few airport reflectors.
The choirs of the University of Carolina will participate in the concert "Students of Terciopelo".
The joint celebration of the International Student Day and the anniversary of the Terciopelo Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Academica festival.
During the same period, twenty corals from high school and university centres will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
"The University of Carolina has a high participation in the festival."
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, in the festival committee is the rector Václav Hampl," said the head of the organization, Jakub Čaloun.
The summit of the entire festival is the free entrance for all audiences to the high school choir concert, which will be held on 17 March at 14 hours before the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The programme includes the participation of the Czech jazzist Karel Ržička and his Celebration Jazz Mass.
At night will be held at the town halls in Vynohrady the concert "Students of Terciopelo", where university choirs will participate, including the choir of the University of Carolina.
The Academy Festival aims not only to celebrate the International Student Day with dignity and to remember the 22nd anniversary of the Terciopelo Revolution, but also to present the choir music to the public at the highest level and to promote collaborative creation among young people.
The main organizer is the Czech Union of Corals in collaboration with the Jan Kepler Secondary Institute.
All the acts were supported by the mayor of Prague, Bohuslav Svoboda, and the rector of the University of Carolina, Václav Hampl.
The Festival will take place between 16 and 20 November between Prague and Pardubice.
The calendar offers, in addition to the celebratory concerts, a whole series of musical events, improvised shows of students and morning concerts.
Interested people will be able to find more information on the festival page www.festaacademica.cz
