How to detect a lie
A look at the most recent headlines tells us how serious and omnipresent lies and lies are in daily life.
Republican presidential candidate Herman Cain is busy exchanging sexual harassment charges with several women; each party accuses of lying to the other.
The administrators of the State University of Pennsylvania have been accused of perjury for allegedly hiding reports that said a retired football coach was sexually assaulting children.
