How has Pearl Jam managed to keep the grunt relevant despite being no longer a fashion?
I think we all always feel a little disconnected from the word grunge.
When I think about it, I remember the bands I mentioned before, like Mudhoney, Soundgarden, Nirvana and all those that came up at the same time, and, if there's relevance now, I think it's a wonderful thing because it's music that's worth listening to and bands like Mudhoney are now doing better music than ever.
At first, his music had a darker content and now it has become more positive.
