The Government of the Great Christian Social Coalition, which is in power in Austria, has decided on Tuesday to include in the Constitution a budgetary "gold rule" to reduce the public deficit and thereby prevent a possible degradation of the Austrian sovereign note by credit rating agencies (triple A).
