The device adopted by the Austrian Government is approaching the "German model", since Germany was the first European country to adopt that type of "rule".
Before 2017, the structural public deficit should decrease by 0.75% each year of gross domestic product (GDP) and, as of 2017, the federal government deficit should not exceed 0.35% of GDP each year, while the regional States, as well as the municipalities, should submit balanced budgets.
